text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia xanthocarpa is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to a small area in the Mid West and Goldfields regions of Western Australia.The rounded or obconic shrub typically grows to a height of 2 to 3 metres (7 to 10 ft). It blooms from July to August and produces yellow flowers.
